modules.description: Parses HTTP accept headers to extract media types and languages from incoming requests. Processes strings in the format "text/html;q=0.9, application/xhtml+xml" into structured lists. Used to dynamically tailor responses based on client preferences, such as serving localized content or formatted data.

Retrieves and sets HTTP Accept headers for media types, charsets, encodings, and languages, including quality values. Functions return parsed lists of supported content types, ordered by quality or as specified in the header. Used to process client preferences in HTTP requests and construct responses with appropriate content negotiation.
